{"TopicId":96334,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Behind The Scenes: \u0026quot;Recover Vessel\u0026quot;","CreatedByName":"CalMacDa","CreatedById":133064,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T06:34:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"CalMacDa","CreatedById":133064,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T06:34:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EWhat Really Happens when you tap the \u0022recover vessel\u0022 button? Hundreds of Kerbals go to work designing and calculating to actually recover the brave Kerbonauts that have returned from their great journey. In this challenge, you will design a ship of any kind that will actually recover the vessel. Here come the hard part. You will be recovering a vessel from the peaks of the mountain range nearest to the KSC. When you take off a plane, right behind you is a range of mountains. This is the range in which the challenge will be conducted from.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003EThe rankings of this challenge are simply based on cost of aircraft.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003ERules:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E- NO MODS!! The stock parts are enough\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E- Recover a bare 3 man capsule from a part of the mountain! Cheats can be used to get it there\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E- Don\u0027t use the debug menu!\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E- There will be separate rankings for those who don\u0027t use the Advanced Grabbing Unit\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E- There will be extra special rankings for those who use rockets. That---is skill\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E- Must safely return all kerbals and capsule. This is the space programs money and reputation on the line!\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EThe capsule must be placed in on this mountain 3000\u002B meters. The placement is irrelevant to the biome!\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003ERequired Screenshots:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EShip in hangar. Must clearly show the cost of the ship\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EShip on runway, ready for launch\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EShip in mid flight, approaching the capsule\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EShip 1km from the capsule\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EShip landed and connected to capsule\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EShip flying back\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EShip landed safely back at the KSC with capsule\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EYour entry will not be ranked if it lacks even 1 of these screenshots.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EThank you for participating and I look forward to seeing all of your entries! \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E-CalMacDa\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003ERankings:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EpercyPrune: 32887.3\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:12px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EFoxster: 46586\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-01-12T02:44:33Z\u0022 title=\u002201/12/2015 02:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 12, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by CalMacDa\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EMaking the\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kahlzun","CreatedById":39989,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T06:40:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESo, anywhere with the \u0027mountain\u0027 biome in that area, or a specific part of the mountains? Are we allowed to put docking ports on the Mk1-2 pod?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECan we see your own attemp?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T10:01:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EInteresting challenge. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDo need to clear up the area though. How about anywhere in the mountains biome? That would be the brown area here:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i395.photobucket.com/albums/pp38/FoxMouldy/Kerbin_zpsa5a3903f.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022Kerbin_zpsa5a3903f.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECan turn this on through alt-F12. Biome can be confirmed with Mechjeb etc. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso - does capsule to be recovered have to be naked i.e. no additional parts attached?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fengist","CreatedById":78435,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T13:09:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYea, I\u0027d like to see his \u0027attempt\u0027 at this as well. The rules are so \u0027ambiguous\u0027 either the door is either wide open or you better be damned good at VTOL\u0027s.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T15:01:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENear - but no goldfish...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i395.photobucket.com/albums/pp38/FoxMouldy/Nearbutnogoldfish_zpsa3054e43.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022Nearbutnogoldfish_zpsa3054e43.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMight have to rethink this. That was my best near-miss after about 25 tries. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUmm...wheels?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CalMacDa","CreatedById":133064,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T17:10:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESorry guys. I revised. Capsule must me 3000m\u002B in altitude on the mountain.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T17:11:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EDid it. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlbum: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://s395.photobucket.com/user/FoxMouldy/slideshow/Recovery\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://s395.photobucket.com/user/FoxMouldy/slideshow/Recovery\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i395.photobucket.com/albums/pp38/FoxMouldy/Recovery/5Landedandconnected_zps12e4e997.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00225Landedandconnected_zps12e4e997.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CalMacDa","CreatedById":133064,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T17:23:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fengist\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Fengist\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EYea, I\u0027d like to see his \u0027attempt\u0027 at this as well. The rules are so \u0027ambiguous\u0027 either the door is either wide open or you better be damned good at VTOL\u0027s.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eokay. I can\u0027t at the moment, due to conflicting plans, but on Monday I will share\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"percyPrune","CreatedById":130676,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-11T19:51:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003Eyou better be damned good at VTOL\u0027s.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFair enough. The \u0022Horseshoe Lifter Mk1\u0022...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/Kijgr#0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/Kijgr#0\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECouldn\u0027t quite get a pic at 1km. Hope 1.135 is close enough. (I was a bit busy at the 1km. mark.) Thanks to Bill, Bob, Buzz and Jeb for being patient.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-01-11T20:02:23Z\u0022 title=\u002201/11/2015 08:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 11, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by percyPrune\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"percyPrune","CreatedById":130676,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-01-12T18:59:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E2nd variant without the Grabber. Bit more expensive though...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/TKGSvyD.png\u0022 alt=\u0022TKGSvyD.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlbum: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/nMXI2#0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/nMXI2#0\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:underline;\u0022\u003EAddition\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E: Hi CalMacDa. I hadn\u0027t realised you were ranking by cost. There were a few twiddly bits on both versions which are just gold plating (emergency parachutes, for instance). They don\u0027t affect the performance so I have knocked them off and removed 2 landing legs to bring the price down. Pic below of the 2nd version in the SPH shows the revised cost. If you want, I will re-run the mission to prove it still works but it would just be more of the same and I don\u0027t want to hog the thread!\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/nMXI2#0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/VSHyxcq.png\u0022 alt=\u0022VSHyxcq.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-01-12T22:09:25Z\u0022 title=\u002201/12/2015 10:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 12, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by percyPrune\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EMade it cheaper!\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}